<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Isoetes</i> <i>bolanderi</i>, <i>Isoetes</i> <i>echinospora</i>, <i>Isoetes</i> <i>howellii</i>, <i>Isoetes</i> <i>nuttallii</i> or <i>Isoetes</i> <i>occidentalis</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Torreyochloa</i> <i>erecta</i>. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 25 cm; cover is open to continuous. </div>
</div>

		
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Submerged beds at permanently flooded and seasonally flooded margins of lakes, ponds, and streams. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes all <i>Isoetes</i> species as OBL plants. </div>
</div>

		
